1827, \"to\": 1919, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The biggest change\", \"from\": 1827, \"to\": 1845}, {\"ngram\": \"Olympics coverage\", \"from\": 1849, \"to\": 1866}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The total run time of the various competitions in the Olympic games will clock in at around 3,800 hours.\", \"from\": 1920, \"to\": 2024, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The total run time\", \"from\": 1920, \"to\": 1938}, {\"ngram\": \"the various competitions\", \"from\": 1942, \"to\": 1966}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympic games\", \"from\": 1970, \"to\": 1987}, {\"ngram\": \"around 3,800 hours\", \"from\": 2005, \"to\": 2023}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The OBS plans to turn that into more than11,000 hours of content-a mixture of live coverage, behind-the-scenes features, narrated analysis, and highlights.\", \"from\": 2025, \"to\": 2180, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2029, \"end\": 2032, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Broadcasting_Services\", \"score\": 0.9902904959084127, \"rank\": 0.009804702894410575, \"text\": \"OBS\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Broadcasting_Services\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Broadcasting_Services\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"more than11,000 hours\", \"from\": 2057, \"to\": 2078}, {\"ngram\": \"content\", \"from\": 2082, \"to\": 2089}, {\"ngram\": \"a mixture\", \"from\": 2090, \"to\": 2099}, {\"ngram\": \"live coverage\", \"from\": 2103, \"to\": 2116}, {\"ngram\": \"the-scenes\", \"from\": 2125, \"to\": 2135}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Anyone tuning in will need a way to sift through it all.\", \"from\": 2182, \"to\": 2238, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Anyone\", \"from\": 2182, \"to\": 2188}, {\"ngram\": \"a way\", \"from\": 2209, \"to\": 2214}]}, {\"sentence\": \"NBC wants to make that easier on its Peacock streaming platform and has debuted a bunch ofnew viewing optionsthat will let users curate their own Olympics coverage, in addition streaming nearly every event live from the Olympics and theParalympics.\", \"from\": 2239, \"to\": 2487, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2239, \"end\": 2242, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC\", \"score\": 0.9973285779363835, \"rank\": 0.002676783878839632, \"text\": \"NBC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"its Peacock streaming platform\", \"from\": 2272, \"to\": 2302}, {\"ngram\": \"a bunch ofnew viewing optionsthat\", \"from\": 2319, \"to\": 2352}, {\"ngram\": \"users\", \"from\": 2362, \"to\": 2367}, {\"ngram\": \"their own Olympics coverage\", \"from\": 2375, \"to\": 2402}, {\"ngram\": \"addition\", \"from\": 2407, \"to\": 2415}, {\"ngram\": \"nearly every event\", \"from\": 2426, \"to\": 2444}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympics\", \"from\": 2455, \"to\": 2467}, {\"ngram\": \"theParalympics\", \"from\": 2472, \"to\": 2486}]}, {\"sentence\": \"(The Paralympics, also taking place in Paris, start on August 28.)\", \"from\": 2488, \"to\": 2554, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2527, \"end\": 2532, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.329582237696005e-14, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"(The Paralympics\", \"from\": 2488, \"to\": 2504}, {\"ngram\": \"place\", \"from\": 2518, \"to\": 2523}, {\"ngram\": \"August\", \"from\": 2543, \"to\": 2549}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In the Peacock Olympics hub, viewers can sort listings by sport, athlete, or country to find the events they want to watch and then add them to a watch list.\", \"from\": 2556, \"to\": 2713, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the Peacock Olympics hub\", \"from\": 2559, \"to\": 2583}, {\"ngram\": \"viewers\", \"from\": 2585, \"to\": 2592}, {\"ngram\": \"listings\", \"from\": 2602, \"to\": 2610}, {\"ngram\": \"sport\", \"from\": 2614, \"to\": 2619}, {\"ngram\": \"athlete\", \"from\": 2621, \"to\": 2628}, {\"ngram\": \"country\", \"from\": 2633, \"to\": 2640}, {\"ngram\": \"the events\", \"from\": 2649, \"to\": 2659}, {\"ngram\": \"a watch list\", \"from\": 2700, \"to\": 2712}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This lets viewers create their own schedule to watch events live, as well as a place where they can come back to watch their chosen events later.\", \"from\": 2714, \"to\": 2859, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"viewers\", \"from\": 2724, \"to\": 2731}, {\"ngram\": \"their own schedule\", \"from\": 2739, \"to\": 2757}, {\"ngram\": \"events\", \"from\": 2767, \"to\": 2773}, {\"ngram\": \"a place\", \"from\": 2791, \"to\": 2798}, {\"ngram\": \"their chosen events\", \"from\": 2833, \"to\": 2852}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Viewers can also watch up to four live events on the same screen using a new Multiview tool that makes it easy to flip between concurrent events.\", \"from\": 2860, \"to\": 3005, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2937, \"end\": 2946, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Amiga_support_and_maintenance_software\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Multiview\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Amiga_support_and_maintenance_software\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Amiga_support_and_maintenance_software\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Viewers\", \"from\": 2860, \"to\": 2867}, {\"ngram\": \"up to four live events\", \"from\": 2883, \"to\": 2905}, {\"ngram\": \"the same screen\", \"from\": 2909, \"to\": 2924}, {\"ngram\": \"concurrent events\", \"from\": 2987, \"to\": 3004}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The OBS is producing its video content in ultrahigh definition and high dynamic range, which should spruce up the level of detail and color in every shot.\", \"from\": 3007, \"to\": 3161, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3011, \"end\": 3014, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Broadcasting_Services\", \"score\": 0.9902904959084127, \"rank\": 0.009804702894410575, \"text\": \"OBS\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Broadcasting_Services\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Broadcasting_Services\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"its video content\", \"from\": 3028, \"to\": 3045}, {\"ngram\": \"ultrahigh definition\", \"from\": 3049, \"to\": 3069}, {\"ngram\": \"high dynamic range\", \"from\": 3074, \"to\": 3092}, {\"ngram\": \"the level\", \"from\": 3117, \"to\": 3126}, {\"ngram\": \"detail\", \"from\": 3130, \"to\": 3136}, {\"ngram\": \"color\", \"from\": 3141, \"to\": 3146}, {\"ngram\": \"every shot\", \"from\": 3150, \"to\": 3160}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Content is also being captured in all manner of formats: vertical video for watching clips on phones, 8K video for the highest-definition broadcasts, and 360-degree shots for truly immersive drama.\", \"from\": 3162, \"to\": 3359, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Content\", \"from\": 3162, \"to\": 3169}, {\"ngram\": \"all manner\", \"from\": 3196, \"to\": 3206}, {\"ngram\": \"formats\", \"from\": 3210, \"to\": 3217}, {\"ngram\": \"vertical video\", \"from\": 3219, \"to\": 3233}, {\"ngram\": \"clips\", \"from\": 3247, \"to\": 3252}, {\"ngram\": \"phones\", \"from\": 3256, \"to\": 3262}, {\"ngram\": \"8K video\", \"from\": 3264, \"to\": 3272}, {\"ngram\": \"the highest-definition broadcasts\", \"from\": 3277, \"to\": 3310}, {\"ngram\": \"360-degree shots\", \"from\": 3316, \"to\": 3332}, {\"ngram\": \"truly immersive drama\", \"from\": 3337, \"to\": 3358}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The OBS says it has more than doubled themulti-camera systemsit uses to capture multiple angles of the action for super-slow-motion replays later.\", \"from\": 3361, \"to\": 3507, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3365, \"end\": 3368, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Broadcasting_Services\", \"score\": 0.9902904959084127, \"rank\": 0.009804702894410575, \"text\": \"OBS\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Broadcasting_Services\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Broadcasting_Services\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"themulti-camera systemsit\", \"from\": 3399, \"to\": 3424}, {\"ngram\": \"multiple angles\", \"from\": 3441, \"to\": 3456}, {\"ngram\": \"the action\", \"from\": 3460, \"to\": 3470}, {\"ngram\": \"super-slow-motion replays\", \"from\": 3475, \"to\": 3500}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It will also use cinematic camera lenses, which are capable of capturing artsier shots, like enhanced depth-of-field changes that you have probably seen in movies.\", \"from\": 3508, \"to\": 3671, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"cinematic camera lenses\", \"from\": 3525, \"to\": 3548}, {\"ngram\": \"artsier shots\", \"from\": 3581, \"to\": 3594}, {\"ngram\": \"field\", \"from\": 3619, \"to\": 3624}, {\"ngram\": \"movies\", \"from\": 3664, \"to\": 3670}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The struggle to make that happen with traditional sports cameras is that the time typically needed to process those complex shots has prevented them from being used in live production.\", \"from\": 3672, \"to\": 3856, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The struggle\", \"from\": 3672, \"to\": 3684}, {\"ngram\": \"traditional sports cameras\", \"from\": 3710, \"to\": 3736}, {\"ngram\": \"the time\", \"from\": 3745, \"to\": 3753}, {\"ngram\": \"those complex shots\", \"from\": 3782, \"to\": 3801}, {\"ngram\": \"live production\", \"from\": 3840, \"to\": 3855}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But the OBS is relying on AI and cloud technologies to speed up the processing time enough to use these shots within its live coverage.\", \"from\": 3857, \"to\": 3992, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3865, \"end\": 3868, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Broadcasting_Services\", \"score\": 0.9902904959084127, \"rank\": 0.009804702894410575, \"text\": \"OBS\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Broadcasting_Services\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Broadcasting_Services\"}, {\"begin\": 3883, \"end\": 3885, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\", \"score\": 0.9999893240016353, \"rank\": 1.0676112177379064e-05, \"text\": \"AI\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"technologies\", \"from\": 3896, \"to\": 3908}, {\"ngram\": \"the processing time\", \"from\": 3921, \"to\": 3940}, {\"ngram\": \"these shots\", \"from\": 3955, \"to\": 3966}, {\"ngram\": \"its live coverage\", \"from\": 3974, \"to\": 3991}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Exarchos says its new processes enable shots that were hitherto impossible to capture and present live, like 360-degree replays that spin the viewer around the athlete while they are sailing through the air.\", \"from\": 3993, \"to\": 4200, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Exarchos\", \"from\": 3993, \"to\": 4001}, {\"ngram\": \"its new processes\", \"from\": 4007, \"to\": 4024}, {\"ngram\": \"shots\", \"from\": 4032, \"to\": 4037}, {\"ngram\": \"360-degree replays\", \"from\": 4102, \"to\": 4120}, {\"ngram\": \"the viewer\", \"from\": 4131, \"to\": 4141}, {\"ngram\": \"the athlete\", \"from\": 4149, \"to\": 4160}, {\"ngram\": \"the air\", \"from\": 4192, \"to\": 4199}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"The effect that exists in theMatrixfilm that you could do in cinema, you can be doing live,\\\" Exarchos says.\", \"from\": 4202, \"to\": 4310, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The effect\", \"from\": 4203, \"to\": 4213}, {\"ngram\": \"theMatrixfilm\", \"from\": 4229, \"to\": 4242}, {\"ngram\": \"cinema\", \"from\": 4264, \"to\": 4270}, {\"ngram\": \"Exarchos\", \"from\": 4296, \"to\": 4304}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The OBS is also recording sounds in 5.1.4 audio, with the goal of capturing immersive audio from the venues during events and during interviews with athletes on the sidelines.\", \"from\": 4312, \"to\": 4487, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4316, \"end\": 4319, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Broadcasting_Services\", \"score\": 0.9902904959084127, \"rank\": 0.009804702894410575, \"text\": \"OBS\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Broadcasting_Services\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Broadcasting_Services\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"sounds\", \"from\": 4338, \"to\": 4344}, {\"ngram\": \"5.1.4 audio\", \"from\": 4348, \"to\": 4359}, {\"ngram\": \"the goal\", \"from\": 4366, \"to\": 4374}, {\"ngram\": \"immersive audio\", \"from\": 4388, \"to\": 4403}, {\"ngram\": \"the venues\", \"from\": 4409, \"to\": 4419}, {\"ngram\": \"events\", \"from\": 4427, \"to\": 4433}, {\"ngram\": \"interviews\", \"from\": 4445, \"to\": 4455}, {\"ngram\": \"athletes\", \"from\": 4461, \"to\": 4469}, {\"ngram\": \"the sidelines\", \"from\": 4473, \"to\": 4486}]}, {\"sentence\": \"That, along with things like augmented-reality stations that give people a view of what it is like on the Olympic grounds, are meant to make those at home feel like they are closer to the games.\", \"from\": 4488, \"to\": 4682, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"things\", \"from\": 4505, \"to\": 4511}, {\"ngram\": \"augmented-reality stations\", \"from\": 4517, \"to\": 4543}, {\"ngram\": \"people\", \"from\": 4554, \"to\": 4560}, {\"ngram\": \"a view\", \"from\": 4561, \"to\": 4567}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympic grounds\", \"from\": 4590, \"to\": 4609}, {\"ngram\": \"home\", \"from\": 4638, \"to\": 4642}, {\"ngram\": \"the games\", \"from\": 4672, \"to\": 4681}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"If we repeat the previous-very successful-games, we have failed,\\\" Exarchos says.\", \"from\": 4684, \"to\": 4765, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the previous-very successful-games\", \"from\": 4698, \"to\": 4732}, {\"ngram\": \"Exarchos\", \"from\": 4751, \"to\": 4759}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Because as in sports, everything is about breaking new ground, breaking new frontiers, and going one step further.\\\"\", \"from\": 4766, \"to\": 4882, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"sports\", \"from\": 4781, \"to\": 4787}, {\"ngram\": \"everything\", \"from\": 4789, \"to\": 4799}, {\"ngram\": \"new ground\", \"from\": 4818, \"to\": 4828}, {\"ngram\": \"new frontiers\", \"from\": 4839, \"to\": 4852}]}, {\"sentence\": \"As you'd expect in 2024, artificial intelligence tools will be used extensively during the Olympics.\", \"from\": 4884, \"to\": 4984, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"artificial intelligence tools\", \"from\": 4909, \"to\": 4938}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympics\", \"from\": 4971, \"to\": 4983}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Broadcasters like the Olympic Broadcasting Service and NBC will use AI to pull together highlights that scrape thousands of hours of footage to find key moments, package them up nicely, and deliver them straight to the viewer.\", \"from\": 4986, \"to\": 5212, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5041, \"end\": 5044, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC\", \"score\": 0.9973285779363835, \"rank\": 0.002676783878839632, \"text\": \"NBC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC\"}, {\"begin\": 5054, \"end\": 5056, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\", \"score\": 0.9999893240016353, \"rank\": 1.0676112177379064e-05, \"text\": \"AI\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Broadcasters\", \"from\": 4986, \"to\": 4998}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympic Broadcasting Service\", \"from\": 5004, \"to\": 5036}, {\"ngram\": \"highlights\", \"from\": 5074, \"to\": 5084}, {\"ngram\": \"thousands\", \"from\": 5097, \"to\": 5106}, {\"ngram\": \"hours\", \"from\": 5110, \"to\": 5115}, {\"ngram\": \"footage\", \"from\": 5119, \"to\": 5126}, {\"ngram\": \"key moments\", \"from\": 5135, \"to\": 5146}, {\"ngram\": \"the viewer\", \"from\": 5201, \"to\": 5211}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Some companies have gone all in on AI offerings; NBC will be using the AI-rendered voice of legendarysportscaster Al Michaelsto narrate its highlights packages on Peacock.\", \"from\": 5213, \"to\": 5384, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5248, \"end\": 5250, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\", \"score\": 0.9999893240016353, \"rank\": 1.0676112177379064e-05, \"text\": \"AI\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\"}, {\"begin\": 5262, \"end\": 5265, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC\", \"score\": 0.9973285779363835, \"rank\": 0.002676783878839632, \"text\": \"NBC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC\"}, {\"begin\": 5376, \"end\": 5383, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Peafowl\", \"score\": 0.9999999999790816, \"rank\": 2.093800791960748e-11, \"text\": \"Peacock\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Peafowl\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Peafowl\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Some companies\", \"from\": 5213, \"to\": 5227}, {\"ngram\": \"the AI-rendered voice\", \"from\": 5280, \"to\": 5301}, {\"ngram\": \"legendarysportscaster Al Michaelsto\", \"from\": 5305, \"to\": 5340}, {\"ngram\": \"its highlights packages\", \"from\": 5349, \"to\": 5372}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The team trained its generative AI voice engine using Michaels' past appearances on television broadcasts, and the results sound smooth yet still unmistakably uncanny.\", \"from\": 5385, \"to\": 5552, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5417, \"end\": 5419, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\", \"score\": 0.9999893240016353, \"rank\": 1.0676112177379064e-05, \"text\": \"AI\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The team\", \"from\": 5385, \"to\": 5393}, {\"ngram\": \"Michaels' past appearances\", \"from\": 5439, \"to\": 5465}, {\"ngram\": \"television broadcasts\", \"from\": 5469, \"to\": 5490}, {\"ngram\": \"the results\", \"from\": 5496, \"to\": 5507}]}, {\"sentence\": \"As you watch the games live, AI will be able to conjure up key info in real time and display it on screen: stats about the athletes, probability percentages that they will make the shot or beat the clock, and artificially augmented views of what is happening on the ground.\", \"from\": 5554, \"to\": 5827, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5583, \"end\": 5585, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\", \"score\": 0.9999893240016353, \"rank\": 1.0676112177379064e-05, \"text\": \"AI\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the games\", \"from\": 5567, \"to\": 5576}, {\"ngram\": \"key info\", \"from\": 5613, \"to\": 5621}, {\"ngram\": \"real time\", \"from\": 5625, \"to\": 5634}, {\"ngram\": \"screen\", \"from\": 5653, \"to\": 5659}, {\"ngram\": \"stats\", \"from\": 5661, \"to\": 5666}, {\"ngram\": \"the athletes\", \"from\": 5673, \"to\": 5685}, {\"ngram\": \"probability percentages\", \"from\": 5687, \"to\": 5710}, {\"ngram\": \"the shot\", \"from\": 5731, \"to\": 5739}, {\"ngram\": \"the clock\", \"from\": 5748, \"to\": 5757}, {\"ngram\": \"views\", \"from\": 5786, \"to\": 5791}, {\"ngram\": \"the ground\", \"from\": 5816, \"to\": 5826}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The AI incursion extends beyond the games; NBC isincorporating AIinto its ad platform, with the goal of better personalizing the ads that play during the breaks.\", \"from\": 5828, \"to\": 5989, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5832, \"end\": 5834, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\", \"score\": 0.9999893240016353, \"rank\": 1.0676112177379064e-05, \"text\": \"AI\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\"}, {\"begin\": 5871, \"end\": 5874, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC\", \"score\": 0.9973285779363835, \"rank\": 0.002676783878839632, \"text\": \"NBC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the games\", \"from\": 5860, \"to\": 5869}, {\"ngram\": \"its ad platform\", \"from\": 5898, \"to\": 5913}, {\"ngram\": \"the goal\", \"from\": 5920, \"to\": 5928}, {\"ngram\": \"the ads\", \"from\": 5953, \"to\": 5960}, {\"ngram\": \"the breaks\", \"from\": 5978, \"to\": 5988}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This exorbitant broadcasting bacchanal is still a training ground for these new technologies.\", \"from\": 5991, \"to\": 6084, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"This exorbitant broadcasting bacchanal\", \"from\": 5991, \"to\": 6029}, {\"ngram\": \"a training ground\", \"from\": 6039, \"to\": 6056}, {\"ngram\": \"these new technologies\", \"from\": 6061, \"to\": 6083}]}, {\"sentence\": \"NBC is using the Olympics as the first major test of its Multiview capability and user customization features, so expect to see those things appear more often in regular live sports broadcasts.\", \"from\": 6085, \"to\": 6278, \"en